data.name: lblHowtoWin.Text
data.value:
How to Win The player with 10 victory points wins
How to Get Victory Points Victory point card (1 point) Have the longest road (1 point) Play three knight cards (2 points) Settlements (1 for the base and 2 for the upgraded(city))
Rolling There are two dies to roll. Each tile is given a number of 2-12, skipping over 7. If the roll matches the tile, the players adjacent to it gets resources. However, when the player rolls a 7, the player that rolled gets to move the thief. The thief steals 1-2 resource points depending on which tile it's on.
Building with Resources G = grain, WL = Wool, L = Lumber, S = ore, B = brick
Road 1 L 1 B
Settlement 1 L 1 B 1 WL 1 G
Upgraded settlement 2 G 3 S
Card 1 WL 1 G 2 S
Cards Knight Purpose: to move the thief to another title.
Monopoly Purpose: player that plays the card chooses which resources they want. Other players that have the resource must give all of it.
Victory Point Purpose: adds victory points for the player. The player who gets ten victory points wins.
Road Building Purpose: player can add two new roads free of cost.
Year of Plenty Purpose: player can choose one of each two resources they want from the bank.
